newsitem.title: JORDAN: Jordan overnight rates tend softer at 5.00-5.50pct.
newsitem.headline: Jordan overnight rates tend softer at 5.00-5.50pct.

text.p: Overnight rates on the Jordanian dinar closed at 5.00-5.50 percent on Tuesday against 5.00-6.00 percent on Monday amid ample dinar funds, dealers said.

Dealers attribute the softer market since the start of the trading week on Saturday to over 13 million dinars of maturing CDs that reverted back to the banking system and were not all tied back in a new 15 million dinar CD auction.
Rates hovered around 7.75-8.50 percent on Thursday, the end of the previous trading week, after a week of tight liquidity.
